pr_body:
This PR includes three new `FeatureConnectors` for graphics related datasets:

- **`Pose`**: `FeatureConnector` for 3D Poses. Currently, this is only a wrapper that stores rotation and translation matrices in a dictionary. However, it can be extended to support other pose representations, like quaternions.
- **`VoxelGrid`**: Stores VoxelGrids of arbitrary size. It is capable of reading Voxels from `.mat` files, like they are provided by Pix3D.
- **`Camera`**: Stores the Calibration matrix K + Pose of the camera. 

Also, unit test for all of the above are provided.

pr_body: This PR introduces the mesh refinement branch of Mesh R-CNN. The logic is implemented as a Keras Layer. Additionally, this PR includes further improvements on the Meshes data structure introduced in #437, e.g. vertex adjacency computation for graph convolutions.

pr_body:
This PR integrates all features from #450, #449, #441 and #437 and provides an Implementation of the 3D Prediction Part of Mesh R-CNN. The implementation provides a config driven approach to model initialisation, that can be extended to provide train/eval specific metadata. 

Note that this Model only contains the 3D shape related branches of Mesh R-CNN. The 2D Backbone with `RoIAlign` is still to be implemented as future work.
